    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Diagnostics Model Years 1999-2000 - ELECTRONIC CONTROL SYSTEM DIAGNOSTICS -
        Circuit Function And Diagnostics - Change Oil Lamp (COL)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Change Oil Lamp (COL)</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Signal Functions</title>
            <figure id="f17503033" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg1/eg1293.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Function Diagram for Change Oil Lamp</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The amber Change Oil Lamp will be illuminated when a customer programmable service interval has been
                exceeded. These limits may be set for vehicle miles, hours, or calculated fuel consumption. These
                service interval limits may be adjusted or the Change Oil Lamp feature may be turned on or off using the
                EST tool.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fault Detection / Management</title>
            <para>The ECM can detect an open COL lamp circuit during a Standard Engine Off Test which automatically
                performs an output circuit check.
            </para>
            <figure id="f17503034" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg1/eg1294A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Circuit Diagram for Change Oil Lamp</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Check COL lamp before doing any diagnostic tests.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
